by romainneutron at 2014-05-09T12:00:16Z

I just updated the PR:
It now uses the existence of the `symfony-var-dir` configuration in `composer.json`'s extras to use the "new directory structure" strategy.

We need to know this information (whether to use the new dir struct or not) on composer install / update because it runs `Sensio\Bundle\DistributionBundle\Composer\ScriptHandler::buildBootstrap` that need the correct bootstrap path to proceed.

